<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 02 at 5:55PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern
Pittsburg County through 630 PM CDT...
At 555 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles northeast of Kiowa to 5 miles north of
Ashland. Movement was south at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Kiowa...                          Ashland...
Pittsburg...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
